ilityTest`, but what about helper classes? If a helper has a main method and isn’t a test, can it be package-private? I feel like all top-level test classes should definitely be public, while a non-test class can be package-private.\n\n**Evaluating process coverage**\n\nI'm thinking about whether forking a child process might lack coverage, especially if an agent isn't linked to that child. That's not ideal. I'm also considering launching the same code in a new thread while adjusting the static state, but that doesn't seem right. I wonder if `ResourceBundle.getBundle` doesn't cache the object. The msgs field could be null if it returns null, but it never does. Let's take a look at the dynamic report format to check coverage by line.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_03e72d197ecc5dca016a1e9fc6fe608197a96da60882ce12e9\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqHp_Zjmg3hcEs97N2CcO7AKhVkNwBaVx71su8TGDceOmW_aTy97d0uvne0-JnfHUHp5V42pl0WQyaGxcvWkNflhdv0bs6pb4k1gBmGIfYz0E4PoItBZ7TwNwDKgFM7Edg9LSiL5FjEDUKwOOexJpEILuwTu6v5OyF9i0K_gFwqwgd9CofhqcKq8NPT7DP5SYUjF8SrrrPpFjbJgiiRTpjyD3nmjgKHNCuZO8-dlyoMZRUIFqlAQFxSwDa6Xi8VitnJ8fpYAHXTb3GCOvYiR0b2Ou-gIKb3bBLMInUI8MK6_JbHeaeXIT5BCLvceUxF1NrZXVVf8baEWZiN6NSlehUycT3jpc9GYDTWoqCU0p5SiHGm77ibVJXdsXkHgQRA3-vP9alBNs0vLLmkweJxETuhL8iuf8bHSiIvcmHuLbYZ4ZE44vi6t5_i17SBfAYc7lLMgYJwVovCKhrfk_JLhOlJ6gaDvKJc18-Z1NQFWda_YGCs0EFVeXGn7HHEYGCTi0pMjgn3d-ajwURfymEbhU2RiraHI2LxQxhQ5Dc3qt5Qtzs1ieYmeDllR4DSCp1qDGzqxXxdiHUxxk818KC-jvYq8XWjL0AFY_5lkNHHsit5QwhqOGpbHQszjOzNM6HAu8Z-Or3R-u7bc4NI2-OOPrt6kFyP9tNgKBfyMQcxShU2EjznaWIEcK-UHj2mkcXPsZ7odXydMxKQCfqsdITDZEvPaDv-apxCthIUkCMq7EQ0NSiYvaS-OIqg0Ig37o7mHsd9ZsnLRHocx1i5h7LuqvOGKReOyqys2ip5SCRy1b6mCXDLWkULS2RPLCd5EWfC9IIb8EqmZ7huqog0hCgLbLEKi_r9DmEoGxdaSvS4Rh-o3HggKDAFh3FoIm_gQPW9dV01wVuY_qEia5fRAfM74HjfzlcD3uWuhOfRLahi3EBc3wetEFzemtd-q6DBYyBst1BDHIw_QTxhUh5PQZTJFO30Vq5azxT3ymZVWkUpd5l7t8AF0fdVyElP5ds-9TB4khzx-JnI3X4-ipuGpYOGKYFsTD5vmGSy7Uc5oWu5pJy08Izoioy_qRkJPKWy2djVB0KSNiMP5l5DaipJIkNg_6AauMp